spanGrp.span: 'My late grandfather, like Don Hualima he didn't go to school.'
uj kayni di' nono' (choy rey, che) jeya kus ney Don Walima kaj eskwelanaw'us.
Mi finado abuelo, como Don Hualima no iba a la escuela.' #
'And he speaks the language, he knows the language well, this Juan Hualima.'
che chonsine bara onaran'us aj chonsinew'us, kuj ney Juan Walima.
''Y l sabe el idioma, lo sabe bien este Juan Hualima' #
'He is better than d. E., he is better.'
choy rey jea uj kayni di' nono'o.
'He didn't know about the school at all.'
kaj rey bispap'us naj rey eskwela rey.
'He didn't even make a little circle, he didn't know it.'
ka rey jisanawa'us beya'ka rey oj di' a:te' kwaj ka: bispapa'us.
'Ni siquiera saba hacer un crculo, no lo saba.' #
'And he was rich, he had many cows.'
che riko uj nono'o, kawra ij wa:ka'us.
'That was when I was a little child, but I already noticed.'
nasko rey dichiyeye tochi', ban jayna to'baycho.
'Eso era cuando yo era una nia pero ya me daba cuenta.' #
joyche is chon komersyante di' juyeni.
'And he traded with the people who ... were rich.'
che usko jayna eney jisana'us oj nego:siyo nij juyeni di' ita:na di' riko buka'.
'Y l haca negocios con la gente que era rica.' #
'Then he just made stripes, he just made stripes.'
jayna usko che ja' pina'us ja'a, pin'us ja'.
'You couldn't cheat him in the deal, you couldn't!'
kaj rey oso'niwa oj enganyarkay'us noj rey nego:siyow'us, rey kaj!
'No le podan engaar con el negocio, no lo podan.' #
'The ones who could write couldn't win over him, never.'
julraw'us ij rey bispa di' benabenpa, ka: rey. jayna(C)
'Los que saban escribir no le podan imponer, nunca.'
'His trading was good, he sold cows, novillos, bulls.'
jayaw oj nego:siyow'us, rimae'us ij waka, nowiyo, weye ij rima'us.
'Sus negocios eran buenos, venda vacas, novillos, toros.' #
'That was when my mother sold one cow.'
nasko jema' rimaewa'nej ma' oj sota'ra di' waka.
'Eso era cuando mi madre vendi una vaca.' #
'One cow was the price of those earrings she gave me.
sota'ra di' waka oj bawra'ij ney monloto di' kaye:wa'ne.
'Una vaca fue el precio de esos aros que me di.' #
'One cow was what the earrings cost.'
sota'ra di' waka oj jankarimea'ij monloto.
'Una vaca lo que costaron los aros.' #
'which I lost when that man "carnevalled" me.'
di' kwalena noj karnabae:wa uj rey itila:kwa.
'los que perd cuando este hombre me hizo el carnaval.' #
'Fue eso lo que vendi mi madre.' #
'because they brought ones of gold, rings and earrings,'
bo joyae'is buka' ij oro buka', (so') sortija che ij monlotowanrani.
'porque trajeron unos de oro, anillos y aros.' #
'and chains was what the traders brought.'
che ij kadena ij joyae'ij buka' komersyante.
'y colgantes, lo que trajeron los comerciantes.' #
jayna yeyna'ne i'ne is ney monlotowanrani.
yeyna'nej ma' is jayna ney monloto.
'She told her father, who was my deceased grandfather,'
jayna kenapa'ne uj papa'ne di' kayni di' nono'o.
'Le cont a su padre que es mi finado abuelo.' #
'She told him that she wanted those earrings.'
Le cont que quera esos aros.' #
'Then he said: Good, daughter, he said.'
jayna usko jankwa us: Dokoy majni, jankwa us.
'Then I will buy you the earrings you want, her father said.'
loy i jaye eney(C) rimenakwa:na nij monloto di' yeynan, jankwa uj papa'ne.
'Entonces te voy a comprar los aros que quieres, dijo su padre.' #
'because he didn't speak Spanish, my grandfather.'
bo ka: rey kstew'uj nono' rey.
'porque l no hablaba espaol, mi abuelo.' #
ka: rey kastew'us, bo chonsine ja'a.
'That was when she could still hear, she wasn't very deaf then.'
nasko dira pawanewa'ne, kaj sinlototo'ne mere'.
'Eso era cuando ella todava poda or, no era tan sorda.' #
'Then he said to her: Good, daughter, now I'll buy what you want.'
jayna eney(C) jankwa us ni'ne jayna: Dokoy majni, nokowaj rimna ij yeynan.
'Entonces le dijo a ella: "Bueno, hija, ahora te compro lo que quieras.' #
'You have a cow that doesn't raise its calves, her calves die (on her), they just die.'
koro'koj wakan di' loy, di' loy(C) eyajkwinwa nikij majniwa'as bo ja' kaykaniyemajcho, kayni ja'a.
'Tienes una vaca que no cra sus becerros, sus becerros mueren noms, solamente mueren.' #
'She bears them and they die, the cow aborts her calves, daughter.'
tami:ti'i, che kayni, o'choyemajcho koj waka, majni.
'los pare y se mueren, la vaca aborta sus cras, hija.' #
'That one you sell as exchange for the earrings you want, he said to her.'
asko nokwa rimaen di' bawra ij monlotowanrani di' yeynan, jankwa us ni'ne.
'Esta vas a vender como cambio para los aros que quieres, le dijo.' #
'That was the exchange for the earrings that I lost that she gave me.'
asko bawra ij monloto di' ij kwalena di' kwaye:wa'ne.
'Eso era el pago de los aros, los que yo perd, los que ella me haba dado.' #
'Then she sold the cow - HE sold it.'
jayna rimae'ne oj waka, jayna rimae'us usko.
'Because she told her father what she wanted.'
bo i'ne kenapa'ne uj papa'ne noj yeyna'ne.
'Porque ella le cont a su padre lo que quera.' #
'Then she wanted a sewing machine that was foot-driven, a sewing machine that is (kicked) (gesture towards feet) while you're sewing.'
jayna rey yeyna'ne oj ma:kina di' e'i, di' ma:kina di' e'i ney naj sita'ojwan.
'Entonces quera una mquina de coser de pie, una mquina de coser que hay que patear cuando uno est cosiendo.' #
'Not with the hands, but foot-driven, the machine.'
ka: nikij chopankwa bo e'i oj ma:kina.
'No con las manos, pero con los pies, la mquina.' #
'She wanted it because they brought that machine as well.'
yeyna'ne bo buka' joyae'is oj ma:kina jema'a.
'Ella lo quera porque tambin trajeron esa mquina.' #
'My grandfather bought the machine for his daughter.'
rimenakwana uj nono'o noj makina'nej majniwa'us.
'Mi abuelo compr la mquina para su hija.' #
'They say that two of these, two novillos were the price of the foot-driven machine.'
Ney(C) ney oyra an ij, oyra ij nowiyo di' bawra oj ma:kina di' e'i.
'Dicen que dos de esos, dos de los novillos eran el pago para la mquina de pie.' #
'My grandfather bought it, he sold ox that were of one yoke, tame ox.'
rimna uj nono', rimae'us ij weye'ne di' sota'tova'ij weye'ne di' manso ij weye'ne.
'Mi abuelo lo compr, vendi bueyes que eran de una yunta, los mismos bueyes.'#
'Yes, they were the price of the machine.'
'Si, eran el pago de la mquina.'#
'And one female cow, that was the price of the earrings she gave to me, the ones I lost.'
che oj sotapoy di' waka di' kweyampoy, asko bawra'ij monloto di' kaye:wa'ne di' ij kwalena.
'Y una vaca que era el pago de los aros que me haba dado, los que perd.'#
'Now never again I put earrings on.'
jayna manra kaj jayna rey dodo'wa ij monloto.
'Ya nunca ms me voy a poner aros.' #
'Only now these, only now, only now.'
'Solo esos ahorita, ahorita noms, ahorita noms.' #
'I don't put just anything on, I don't buy the fantasy ones, I don't want that.'
ka: rey do'nawa, rimenawa rey ja' ij fantasiya rey ka: yeyeywa.
'No me pongo ninguna cosa noms, no compro los de fantasa, no quiero eso.'#
'Because they damage my ears when I put them on.'
bo denden ij lototo noj do'nawa.
'Porque me lastiman mis orejas cuando me los pongo.'
